 to open back up.";i:17;s:112:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse whenever it hits an obstruction such as the driveway or ground.";i:18;s:69:"This is the most common problem that your door wont open all the way.";i:19;s:208:"To give you information about these the travel limit controls how far your garage door opens and closes during its operation while force limit controls how much pull is needed to get the door completely open.";i:20;s:60:"You may check the owners manual on how to do the adjustment.";i:21;s:183:"Incorrect travel settings When your garage door is installed the opener is programmed with a number that indicates how far down the door is expected to travel before its fully closed.";i:22;s:167:"If the door closes before that set distance has been completed then the opener thinks theres an error and automatically reverses to prevent property damages or injury.";i:23;s:127:"If the door closes while holding the button pressed you are likely having one of the following issues with your safety sensors.";i:24;s:53:"The solution is usually one or more of the following.";i:25;s:60:"The sensors are dirty - Wipe lenses with a clean soft cloth.";i:26;s:103:"They are misaligned This is the most likely problem and the most common issue with Garage Door openers.";i:27;s:45:"You push the button to close the garage door.";i:28;s:63:"It goes partway down reverses direction and goes back up again.";i:29;s:73:"This is almost always the result of a dirty or obstructed safety feature.";i:30;s:76:"Another common cause of garage doors acting this way is a faulty RPM sensor.";i:31;s:91:"Consult your owners manual or a trained garage door technician in replacing the RPM sensor.";i:32;s:74:"Parts can be purchased in online stores or directly from the manufacturer.";i:33;s:60:"If this has been helpful please click the green accept icon.";i:34;s:40:"Try to operate the garage door manually.";i:35;s:76:"This helps you determine if the problem is related to the door or the motor.";i:36;s:119:"The garage door can be operated manually by disconnecting the garage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:37;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:38;s:66:"Check the alignment of the safety sensors across the door opening.";i:39;s:106:"If they flicker just as the door is closing it can think there is something in the way causing it to open.";i:40;s:64:"Also check the motors torque limit and the down sensor position.";i:41;s:121:"One of the most common issues that a homeowner will encounter with their garage door is that it does not close correctly.";i:42;s:161:"It could be that it starts to close stops and starts again or the garage door might close all the way down and then it goes back up again into the open position.";i:43;s:58:"The garage door opener has a safety feature built into it.";i:44;s:79:"If it senses an obstruction while closing it will reverse to the open position.";i:45;s:69:"You have two adjustments for this feature down travel and down force.";i:46;s:85:"If the door is closing completely then reversing your down travel is adjusted to low.";i:47;s:38:"Here are some symptoms of the problem.";i:48;s:39:"The garage door goes down then back up.";i:49;s:49:"Your garage door opens immediately after closing.";i:50;s:40:"The garage door keeps going up and down.";i:51;s:47:"Your garage door opens when it hits the ground.";i:52;s:39:"Garage door opener keeps going back up.";i:53;s:140:"Turn the down limit switch screw clockwise one turn with a flat blade screwdriver if the garage door closes and then begins to open back up.";i:54;s:49:"The garage door will automatically go in reverse.";i:55;s:85:"Garage Door sometimes opens a few inches and stops then closes and opens all the way.";i:56;s:96:"Can happen either from the wired connector in the garage or one of the remotes from the outside.";i:57;s:72:"Sometimes its fixed by clicking again the door closes then continues to.";i:58;s:14:"Answer 1 of 6.";i:59;s:119:"What causes my garage door to close and soon as it comes down and touches the bottom it will start going back up again.";i:60;s:49:"There are safety features on garage door openers.";i:61;s:91:"Typically when you trigger one the lights will blink and the door will open or stop moving.";i:62;s:16:"One of the safe.";i:63;s:86:"What to Do When Your Garage Door Opens and Closes by Itself Check With Your Neighbors.";i:64;s:91:"In rare instances a nearby neighbor may have a garage door opener set to the same wireless.";i:65;s:27:"Inspect the Control Wiring.";i:66;s:86:"An exposed spot or a short circuit in the small-gauge wire that leads from the garage.";i:67;s:157:"My garage door closes most of the way then goes back up again On Sectional doors- The most common reason I see for this situation is binding torsion springs.";i:68;s:114:"If you havent had your door properly serviced in a long time than your springs may have a buildup of surface rust.";}}